text.tspan: Pitch: It’s lunchtime in the cafeteria, and
you’ve got to feed all the hungry kids.
But none of them will come up to get
their food, so you have to fling the sloppy
joes at them. Hurry, before they start
crying, and careful not to overfeed anyone,
they’ll explode! Can you survive long enough to
make it to the lunch rush bonus round?
My priority here was UX. Did users understand
how to play it without a lengthy explanation?
Was it different from the other games on their
phone? Did they want to play it again? Ensuring
a game is fun isn’t exactly a concrete goal, so
the only way I could determine its level of
funness was to make everyone I knew playtest
it. If you knew me that summer, I’m sorry.
